All three FTD subgroups were significantly impaired in their confrontation naming relative to the performance of healthy seniors
Significant cortical atrophy in subgroups of patients with FTD
All FTD patient subgroups showed significant cortical atrophy in the left anterior temporal cortex.

Areas of cortical atrophy in NON-APH were also seen in anterior, dorsolateral, and insula regions of the right frontal lobe, the insula region of the left frontal lobe, and the left parahippocampal region
Direct correlations of naming difficulty and cortical volume that corresponded to areas of gray matter atrophy

This included: in SD, the lateral region of the left temporal lobe; in PNFA, inferior, orbital, dorsolateral, and premotor regions of the left frontal lobe, and the left anterior temporal cortex, and in NON-APH, the right dorsolateral prefrontal cortex and left anterior temporal cortex.
